<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - MANIFOLDS AND EXHAUST GAS RECIRCULATION (EGR) - Inspection -
        Exhaust Gas Recirculation Cooler
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Cooler</title>
        <figure id="f2050395" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd17/D1702.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 84. EGR cooler with pressure test plates installed</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR Cooler Test Plate (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR cooler assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air pressure regulator</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install an EGR Cooler Test Plate to each end of the EGR cooler assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes. Limit
                    compressed air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach an air pressure regulator to the EGR cooler. Connect to shop air supply and adjust
                air pressure to approximately 413 kPa (60 psi).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Completely submerge EGR cooler in sink or large container of water. Inspect for air bubbles
                coming from coolant passages. Replace if necessary.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Return EGR cooler assembly to service if no leaks are detected. If leaks are detected,
                replace entire cooler assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
